cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.AR 

This paper discusses the performance analysis of a communication system that involves network function virtualization and Multi-access edge computing (MEC) for future mobile networks supporting Internet of Things. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the analysis of queueing models for processing and transmission flows, which falls under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the impact of traffic flow control on critical performance metrics, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves the development of closed-form expressions for performance metrics, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper also involves the analysis of virtual network functions, which falls under the category of cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
